verbose_text: In our multivariate analysis, the plasma ESR level was associated only with the percentage of time spent at a SpO 2 below 90% (P = 0.007; correlation coefficient, beta = 0.369; 95% confidence interval, 0.043-0.254) and age (P = 0.001; correlation coefficient, beta = 0.463; 95% confidence interval, 0.153-0.552) in the obese group.
